CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1958, pg. A24 reads: "Receives Trophy - Commander's Trophy for most outstanding National Guard unit of Army Air Defense Commons is presented to Col. Paul E. Benson, commanding officer of the 708th Nike Missile Battalion, in a ceremony on the University of Pittsburgh campus. Congratulating Col. Benson is Lieut. Gen. Charles E. Hart. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Five men dressed in U. S. Army uniforms with patches and pins inscribed "Army ROTC" standing on stone patio of University of Pittsburgh Cathedral of Learning with Heinz Chapel in background, Oakland
